am Nash, CEO of <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/adamnash">Daffy</a>, a company that helps people give away their money. Here&#8217;s the Spotify link:</p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a717bd4a22a7a60cad9fee31a&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E10: DM Debates, AI, and Tech Downturns with Adam Nash, CEO of Daffy&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/1m4tXi3rWcWsFYCqnuOyJD&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/1m4tXi3rWcWsFYCqnuOyJD" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>And here are <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/e10-dm-debates-ai-and-tech-downturns-with-adam-nash/id1696419056?i=1000627621538">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xDXOYdRAbWs">YouTube</a>. Erik wanted it to be a &#8220;debate&#8221;, but it turned out we didn&#8217;t really have much to disagree about. </p><p>Anyway, here&#8217;s our regular weekly Econ 102 episode, which is basically a recap of my recent post about why people in the tech world shouldn&#8217;t fall for Vivek Ramaswamy:</p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8a4ca5ff3e9222eb77a125cff7&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E11: Why Vivek is the Wrong Candidate, the new China-Russia Axis, and Ranking Presidents&#8217; Foreign Policy&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/6AgvXSnkrpt9vFZpVxr3sG&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/6AgvXSnkrpt9vFZpVxr3sG" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>And here are <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/e11-fact-checking-vivek-the-new-china-russia-axis/id1696419056?i=1000628389166">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2B6oL06dmDA">YouTube</a> links.</p><p>Finally, Brad DeLong and I have another episode of Hexapodia! </p><div class="embedded-post-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:137076144,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://braddelong.substack.com/p/podcast-hexapodia-liii-rule-1-no&quot;,&quot;publication_id&quot;:47874,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Brad DeLong's Grasping Reality&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ffde2453e-9c18-4560-82ca-8b77ae62ef5b_1280x1280.png&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;PODCAST: Hexapodia LIII: Rule #1: No Schmittposting!&quot;,&quot;truncated_body_text&quot;:&quot;Listen now (71 mins) | Liberals vs. leftists once again, with the principal conclusion being that trying to find and join your tribe by shouting online&#8212;Schmittian picking-an-enemy as the core of your identity&#8212;is no way to &#8230;&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;2023-09-15T20:59:09.778Z&quot;,&quot;like_count&quot;:12,&quot;comment_count&quot;:14,&quot;bylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:16879,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Brad DeLong&quot;,&quot;handle&quot;:&quot;delongonsubstack&quot;,&quot;previous_name&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://bucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ea5ae644-9822-4ca5-ac6b-e18c017d8fbc_1189x1208.png&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Author of Slouching Towards Utopia: An Economic History of the 20th Century, sometime Deputy Assistant Secretary of the U.S. Treasury, too online since 1995, UC Berkeley economic historian&quot;,&quot;profile_set_up_at&quot;:&quot;2021-04-22T17:45:51.845Z&quot;,&quot;publicationUsers&qu